---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const title = "True Residential Appliance Repair Los Angeles | R-290 Certified Specialists";
const description = "Expert True Residential appliance repair in Los Angeles. R-290 certified technicians for refrigerators, wine cabinets, freezers & outdoor units. Commercial heritage, residential precision. Same-day service. Call (626) 376-4458.";
const phone = "(626) 376-4458";
const phoneRaw = "6263764458";
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>

<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "HomeAndConstructionBusiness",
  "name": "Same Day Appliance Repair — True Residential Specialist",
  "url": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brand-true-residential-appliance-repair/",
  "telephone": "+16263764458",
  "address": {
    "@type": "PostalAddress",
    "addressLocality": "Los Angeles",
    "addressRegion": "CA",
    "postalCode": "90001",
    "addressCountry": "US"
  },
  "areaServed": ["Los Angeles County", "Orange County", "Ventura County"],
  "priceRange": "$$",
  "openingHours": "Mo-Sa 08:00-20:00",
  "hasOfferCatalog": {
    "@type": "OfferCatalog",
    "name": "True Residential Repair Services",
    "itemListElement": [
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"True Residential Refrigerator Repair"}},
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"True Residential Wine Cabinet Repair"}},
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"True Residential Freezer Repair"}},
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"True Residential Beverage Center Repair"}},
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"True Residential Outdoor Refrigerator Repair"}},
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"True Residential Undercounter Repair"}}
    ]
  }
}
</script>

<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How much does True Residential appliance repair cost in Los Angeles?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Most True Residential repairs run $175–$620. Common fixes like a temperature sensor, door gasket, fan motor, or evaporator defrost service are on the lower end. Compressor or sealed system work runs higher. Diagnostic fee is $89, waived when you proceed. Written flat-rate estimate before work begins."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What is R-290 refrigerant and why does it matter for True Residential service?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "True Residential uses R-290 — propane — as the refrigerant in many of their residential products. R-290 is an eco-friendly hydrocarbon refrigerant with a global warming potential near zero. Because propane is flammable, working with R-290 sealed systems requires specific safety certification. Technicians without R-290 certification cannot legally or safely work on the sealed system. We are R-290 certified for all True Residential sealed system service."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Is True Residential the same company as True Manufacturing (commercial refrigeration)?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes. True Residential is the residential line from True Manufacturing, founded in 1945 in Springfield, Missouri. True Manufacturing builds refrigeration equipment for commercial kitchens, restaurants, and foodservice operations worldwide. True Residential applies that same commercial engineering — stainless steel interiors, heavy-duty compressors, professional-grade sealed systems — to residential products. The heritage explains why True Residential refrigerators perform and last the way they do."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Do you repair True Residential outdoor refrigerators?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes — outdoor True Residential service is a specific part of our scope. True's outdoor-rated units are weatherproofed for exterior installation, but LA's coastal salt air and Santa Ana wind conditions create accelerated wear on outdoor condenser systems. We treat outdoor True Residential service with the same coastal protocols we use for all outdoor luxury appliances."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What makes True Residential refrigerators different to service?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Three things distinguish True Residential service from standard residential refrigerator work: R-290 hydrocarbon refrigerant (requires specific certification for sealed system work), stainless steel interior construction (from commercial heritage — different thermal properties than plastic-lined units), and European-style auto-close door hinges (different failure modes than American-style hinges). We're trained and equipped for all three."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Can you service True Residential wine cabinets for both zones?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes. True Residential dual-zone wine cabinets use two independent temperature circuits — upper and lower zones maintain different temperatures simultaneously. Zone-specific failures (where one zone drifts while the other holds temperature) indicate a zone-specific sensor or damper issue, not a compressor failure. We test both zones independently and diagnose at the zone level before any sealed-system assessment."
      }
    }
  ]
}
</script>

<style>
  :root {
    --red: #C8102E;
    --black: #0a0a0a;
    --gray: #f5f5f5;
    --border: #e2e2e2;
    --text: #1a1a1a;
    --muted: #6b6b6b;
  }
  * { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
  body { font-family: 'Barlow', 'Inter', system-ui, sans-serif; color: var(--text); }

  .top-bar { background: var(--red); padding: 8px 24px; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; font-size: 13px; color: #fff; }
  .top-bar a { color: #fff; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 700; }

  .hero { background: var(--black); padding: 72px 24px 64px; color: #fff; }
  .hero-inner { max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto; display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 420px; gap: 48px; align-items: center; }
  .hero-eyebrow { font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.15em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--red); margin-bottom: 16px; }
  .hero-title { font-size: clamp(32px, 5vw, 52px); font-weight: 900; line-height: 1.05; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: -0.02em; margin-bottom: 20px; }
  .hero-title span { color: var(--red); }
  .hero-sub { font-size: 17px; line-height: 1.6; color: #aaa; margin-bottom: 32px; max-width: 540px; }
  .hero-cta-group { display: flex; gap: 16px; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .btn-primary { display: inline-block; background: var(--red); color: #fff; padding: 14px 28px; font-size: 15px; font-weight: 700; text-decoration: none; letter-spacing: 0.04em; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .btn-secondary { display: inline-block; border: 1px solid #555; color: #ccc; padding: 14px 28px; font-size: 15px; font-weight: 600; text-decoration: none; letter-spacing: 0.04em; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .hero-badge-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 12px; }
  .hero-badge { background: #161616; border: 1px solid #2a2a2a; padding: 16px 18px; }
  .badge-num { font-size: 28px; font-weight: 900; color: var(--red); line-height: 1; margin-bottom: 4px; }
  .badge-label { font-size: 12px; color: #888; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; }

  .trust-bar { background: var(--red); padding: 14px 24px; }
  .trust-bar-inner { max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 8px; }
  .trust-item { color: #fff; font-size: 13px; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: 0.04em; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .trust-item::before { content: "✓ "; }

  .section { padding: 64px 24px; }
  .section-gray { background: var(--gray); }
  .section-black { background: var(--black); color: #fff; }
  .section-inner { max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .section-num { font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.15em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--red); margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .section-title { font-size: clamp(24px, 3.5vw, 36px); font-weight: 900; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: -0.01em; margin-bottom: 20px; }
  .section-black .section-title { color: #fff; }
  .section-lead { font-size: 17px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--muted); max-width: 760px; margin-bottom: 40px; }
  .section-black .section-lead { color: #999; }

  /* Heritage comparison */
  .heritage-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 1px; background: #2a2a2a; border: 1px solid #2a2a2a; margin-top: 28px; }
  .heritage-card { background: #161616; padding: 24px; }
  .heritage-label { font-size: 10px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.12em; color: var(--red); margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .heritage-title { font-size: 17px; font-weight: 900; text-transform: uppercase; color: #fff; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .heritage-desc { font-size: 13px; color: #777; line-height: 1.6; }

  .tip-block { border-left: 3px solid var(--red); background: #fff8f8; padding: 18px 20px; margin: 32px 0; max-width: 760px; }
  .tip-label { font-size: 10px; font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.15em; color: var(--red); margin-bottom: 6px; }
  .tip-text { font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.65; color: var(--text); }
  .tip-r290 { border-color: #2a7a4a; background: #f0fff5; }
  .tip-r290 .tip-label { color: #2a7a4a; }
  .tip-blue { border-color: #3a7bd5; background: #f0f7ff; }
  .tip-blue .tip-label { color: #3a7bd5; }

  .services-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(300px, 1fr)); gap: 1px; background: var(--border); border: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .service-card { background: #fff; padding: 28px 24px; }
  .service-icon { font-size: 28px; margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .service-name { font-size: 16px; font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.04em; margin-bottom: 10px; color: var(--text); }
  .service-desc { font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.65; color: var(--muted); margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .service-issues { font-size: 12px; color: var(--red); font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; }

  .features-2col { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 48px; align-items: start; }
  .features-list { list-style: none; }
  .features-list li { padding: 14px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid #2a2a2a; font-size: 15px; color: #ccc; display: flex; gap: 12px; }
  .features-list li::before { content: "→"; color: var(--red); flex-shrink: 0; }

  .problems-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(260px, 1fr)); gap: 16px; margin-top: 32px; }
  .problem-card { border: 1px solid var(--border); background: #fff; padding: 20px; }
  .problem-title { font-size: 14px; font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; margin-bottom: 8px; color: var(--text); }
  .problem-cause { font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .problem-tag { display: inline-block; font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; padding: 3px 8px; color: #fff; }
  .tag-common { background: var(--red); }
  .tag-r290 { background: #2a7a4a; }
  .tag-outdoor { background: #7a5a14; }
  .tag-wine { background: #5a2a7a; }

  .pricing-table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin-top: 24px; }
  .pricing-table th { background: var(--text); color: #fff; text-align: left; padding: 12px 16px; font-size: 12px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; }
  .pricing-table td { padding: 14px 16px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); font-size: 14px; }
  .pricing-table tr:last-child td { border-bottom: none; }
  .pricing-table tr:nth-child(even) td { background: var(--gray); }
  .price-range { font-weight: 700; color: var(--red); }

  .why-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(220px, 1fr)); gap: 24px; margin-top: 32px; }
  .why-card { border-left: 3px solid var(--red); padding: 20px; background: #fff; }
  .why-icon { font-size: 24px; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .why-title { font-size: 14px; font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .why-desc { font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.6; }

  .reviews-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(300px, 1fr)); gap: 20px; margin-top: 32px; }
  .review-card { background: #fff; border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 24px; }
  .review-stars { color: var(--red); font-size: 18px; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .review-text { font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--text); margin-bottom: 14px; }
  .review-author { font-size: 12px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--muted); }

  .repairs-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(300px, 1fr)); gap: 1px; background: var(--border); border: 1px solid var(--border); margin-top: 32px; }
  .repair-item { background: #fff; padding: 24px; }
  .repair-appliance { font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; color: var(--red); margin-bottom: 6px; }
  .repair-issue { font-size: 15px; font-weight: 800; color: var(--text); margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .repair-detail { font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.6; }
  .repair-meta { margin-top: 12px; font-size: 12px; font-weight: 600; color: #aaa; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; }

  .faq-list { margin-top: 32px; }
  .faq-item { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 20px 0; }
  .faq-q { font-size: 16px; font-weight: 800; color: var(--text); margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .faq-a { font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--muted); max-width: 760px; }

  .nearby-grid { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 8px; margin-top: 20px; }
  .nearby-chip { background: var(--gray); border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 8px 14px; font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted); text-decoration: none; font-weight: 600; }
  .nearby-chip:hover { border-color: var(--red); color: var(--red); }

  .bottom-cta { background: var(--black); padding: 72px 24px; text-align: center; color: #fff; }
  .bottom-cta-title { font-size: clamp(28px, 4vw, 44px); font-weight: 900; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: -0.01em; margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .bottom-cta-title span { color: var(--red); }
  .bottom-cta-sub { font-size: 17px; color: #888; margin-bottom: 32px; }
  .cta-phone-large { display: inline-block; font-size: clamp(28px, 4vw, 42px); font-weight: 900; color: #fff; text-decoration: none; letter-spacing: -0.01em; margin-bottom: 24px; border-bottom: 2px solid var(--red); padding-bottom: 4px; }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .hero-inner { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .hero-badge-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; }
    .features-2col { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .heritage-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .trust-bar-inner { flex-direction: column; gap: 6px; }
  }
</style>

<!-- TOP BAR -->
<div class="top-bar">
  <span>Mon–Sat 8am–8pm · Los Angeles &amp; Southern California</span>
  <a href={`tel:${phoneRaw}`}>{phone}</a>
</div>

<!-- HERO -->
<section class="hero">
  <div class="hero-inner">
    <div>
      <div class="hero-eyebrow">True Residential Appliance Repair — Los Angeles</div>
      <h1 class="hero-title">
        True Residential.<br/>
        <span>R-290 Certified.</span><br/>
        Commercial Heritage.
      </h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        True Residential is the home line from the same company that refrigerates Michelin-starred kitchens since 1945. The R-290 hydrocarbon refrigerant they use requires certified technicians — most general appliance companies can't legally touch the sealed system. We can. Same day across LA.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-cta-group">
        <a href={`tel:${phoneRaw}`} class="btn-primary">Call {phone}</a>
        <a href="/book/" class="btn-secondary">Book Online</a>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="hero-badge-grid">
      <div class="hero-badge">
        <div class="badge-num">R-290</div>
        <div class="badge-label">Certified</div>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-badge">
        <div class="badge-num">OEM</div>
        <div class="badge-label">True Parts</div>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-badge">
        <div class="badge-num">90-Day</div>
        <div class="badge-label">Warranty</div>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-badge">
        <div class="badge-num">$89</div>
        <div class="badge-label">Diagnostic Fee</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- TRUST BAR -->
<div class="trust-bar">
  <div class="trust-bar-inner">
    <span class="trust-item">Licensed &amp; Insured · CSLB #1138898</span>
    <span class="trust-item">R-290 Hydrocarbon Certified</span>
    <span class="trust-item">All True Residential Models</span>
    <span class="trust-item">Indoor &amp; Outdoor Units</span>
    <span class="trust-item">Flat-Rate Written Estimate</span>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- 01 — ABOUT TRUE RESIDENTIAL -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="section-num">01 — About True Residential</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">From Commercial Kitchens to Your Home. Same Engineering.</h2>
    <p class="section-lead">
      True Manufacturing was founded in 1945 in Springfield, Missouri, and became one of the world's leading commercial refrigeration manufacturers — building the reach-in coolers and prep table refrigerators used in restaurants, hotels, grocery stores, and Michelin-starred kitchens worldwide. True Residential is the brand's direct entry into the home market: the same heavy-duty compressors, stainless steel interiors, and professional-grade sealed systems, packaged into undercounter and column refrigerators, wine cabinets, freezers, and beverage centers designed for residential installation.
    </p>
    <p class="section-lead">
      What sets True Residential apart technically — and what makes service different — is the use of R-290 refrigerant (propane) rather than the HFC refrigerants most residential brands use. R-290 has a global warming potential near zero, making it one of the most environmentally responsible refrigerants available. It also requires technicians with specific R-290 safety certification to perform any sealed system work, because propane is flammable. Most general appliance technicians aren't certified. We are.
    </p>

    <div class="heritage-grid">
      <div class="heritage-card">
        <div class="heritage-label">The Commercial Heritage</div>
        <div class="heritage-title">True Manufacturing · Since 1945</div>
        <div class="heritage-desc">Commercial refrigeration manufacturer serving restaurants, hotels, grocery chains, and foodservice operations worldwide for nearly 80 years. The compressor quality, stainless steel construction, and sealed system engineering come from this lineage — designed to run continuously in demanding commercial environments, not just the 8–12 hours a day a home refrigerator operates.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="heritage-card">
        <div class="heritage-label">The Residential Application</div>
        <div class="heritage-title">True Residential · Home Luxury Line</div>
        <div class="heritage-desc">Undercounter refrigerators, column refrigerators and freezers, wine cabinets, beverage centers, and outdoor-rated units. Stainless steel interior lining instead of plastic. R-290 refrigerant. EU-style auto-close hinges. Panel-ready options. The commercial engineering applied to residential installations — butler pantries, outdoor kitchens, pool houses, custom bar rooms.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="tip-block tip-r290" style="margin-top:32px">
      <div class="tip-label">🌿 R-290 Refrigerant — Why Most Technicians Can't Service It</div>
      <div class="tip-text">True Residential uses R-290 — propane — as the primary refrigerant across most of their product line. R-290 is a hydrocarbon refrigerant with a global warming potential of 3 (versus 1,430 for R-134a used in most residential appliances). It's also flammable. Working with an R-290 sealed system requires specific safety certification, specialized recovery equipment, and adherence to strict ventilation protocols. A technician who opens a True Residential sealed system without R-290 certification is creating a real safety risk — and most general appliance technicians don't hold this certification. We do. Every sealed system service call on a True Residential unit is performed by our R-290 certified technicians only.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 02 — SERVICES -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="section-num">02 — Services</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">Every True Residential Appliance We Service</h2>
    <p class="section-lead">All True Residential models — indoor, outdoor, built-in, freestanding. R-290 sealed system work, component service, and annual maintenance. Same-day across Los Angeles County.</p>

    <div class="services-grid">
      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">❄️</div>
        <div class="service-name">Refrigerator &amp; Freezer Repair</div>
        <div class="service-desc">True Residential column refrigerators, undercounter refrigerators, column freezers, and drawer freezers. The stainless steel interior construction holds temperature more evenly than plastic-lined units but also means different thermal dynamics when diagnosing temperature drift. Condenser coil maintenance on True Residential units is critical — the commercial-heritage compressor runs efficiently when airflow is clean, and degrades faster when coils accumulate dust in LA's particulate environment.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Common: temperature drift · not cooling · R-290 sealed system (certified only) · condenser coil service · door gasket · EU hinge fault · fan motor · defrost system · temperature sensor</div>
      </div>

      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">🍷</div>
        <div class="service-name">Wine Cabinet Repair</div>
        <div class="service-desc">True Residential single-zone and dual-zone wine cabinets. Dual-zone models maintain two independent temperature targets simultaneously — the upper zone for serving-temperature whites and the lower zone for cellar-temperature reds. Zone-specific drift (where one zone loses temperature accuracy while the other holds) points to a zone-specific damper or sensor fault, not the compressor or R-290 system. We test each zone independently before any sealed system diagnosis.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Common: zone temperature drift · dual-zone calibration · vibration (low-vibration compressor service) · door gasket · fan motor · temperature sensor · lighting · condenser service</div>
      </div>

      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">🍺</div>
        <div class="service-name">Beverage Center Repair</div>
        <div class="service-desc">True Residential undercounter beverage centers — single-zone and multi-zone configurations for beer, wine, and specialty beverages. Beverage centers in LA's outdoor kitchen installations experience additional thermal stress from ambient heat during summer months. The condenser in an outdoor-environment beverage center works significantly harder than one in a climate-controlled interior — we factor this into every outdoor True Residential service call.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Common: not cooling · temperature inconsistency · coil service (outdoor ambient) · door gasket · fan · temperature sensor · control board · LED lighting</div>
      </div>

      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">🌿</div>
        <div class="service-name">Outdoor Unit Repair</div>
        <div class="service-desc">True Residential outdoor-rated refrigerators, freezers, and beverage centers — built for exterior installation in outdoor kitchens, pool houses, and patio bar areas. True's outdoor units are weatherproofed with stainless exteriors and sealed electronics, but LA's coastal salt air and Santa Ana wind events create specific failure patterns: condenser corrosion at coastal properties, ash accumulation after wind events, and UV degradation of door seals over time.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Common: condenser coil service · coastal corrosion (salt air) · door gasket UV degradation · not cooling · temperature drift · fan motor · control board · LED lighting · drain line</div>
      </div>

      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">🧊</div>
        <div class="service-name">R-290 Sealed System Service</div>
        <div class="service-desc">When True Residential cooling performance has degraded to the point that component-level fixes (coil cleaning, sensor replacement, fan service) don't resolve the issue, sealed system work is required. R-290 sealed system service — refrigerant recovery, leak repair, recharge — requires our R-290 certified technicians and specialized equipment. We are one of the few appliance service companies in Los Angeles with full R-290 sealed system certification and tooling.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">R-290 recovery and recharge · refrigerant leak detection · evaporator service · condenser replacement · compressor service (R-290 rated only)</div>
      </div>

      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">🔧</div>
        <div class="service-name">Annual Maintenance</div>
        <div class="service-desc">True Residential's commercial heritage means these units are built for continuous operation — but that doesn't mean maintenance-free. Annual service extends unit life significantly: condenser coil cleaning (critical in LA's dusty environment), door gasket inspection, temperature calibration verification, drain line clearing, and R-290 system pressure check. We offer annual service packages for True Residential installations throughout LA.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Condenser coil cleaning · gasket inspection · temperature calibration · drain line service · R-290 pressure verification · EU hinge adjustment · LED inspection · exterior weatherproofing check</div>
